SIMPLE: graving
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Graving
<hw>Grav"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Grave</er>
to clean.]</ety> <def>The act of cleaning a ship's bottom.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Graving dock</b></col>. <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <cd>See under
Dock.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Graving</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Graving
<hw>Grav"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Grave</er> to
dig.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or art of carving figures in hard
substances, especially by incision or in intaglio.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is graved or carved.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Skillful to . . . <qex>grave</qex> any manner of
<qex>graving</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>2 Chron. ii. 14.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Impression, as upon the mind or heart.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>New <qex>gravings</qex> upon their souls.</q> <rj><qau>Eikon
Basilike</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gravitate</ent>⟦br⟧
